reviews.text: But I liked it so much, I bought another! I’m not sure that the functionality was ever explained, fully in other reviews. When the switch is open (lights are off), there is a fairly bright LED illuminating the translucent switch. When the switch is closed (lights go on) the translucent switch glows just slightly. When it’s “broken” (after a few months of normal use), the switch works fine, but there’s no translucent-switch illumination , at all. That’s when Karl buys another one.

reviews.productTitle: Leviton L1463-2C 15 Amp, 120 Volt, Toggle LED Illuminated 3-Way Switch, Residential Grade, Grounding, Clear
reviews.text: I converted a 3-way switched circuit into a 4-way switched circuit. I wanted to be able to turn the laundry room lights on from within the garage, since that is the way we enter the house the most. Prior to converting the switches, we had to open the door into the laundry room and reach around the corner to flip on the lights. Not always easy as you arrive home from the grocery store and are loaded down with grocery bags going into the house. By having a lighted switch in the garage, it is easy to determine if the laundry room light is on and if not, turn it on. So now, this switch met our need.

reviews.productTitle: Leviton L1463-2C 15 Amp, 120 Volt, Toggle LED Illuminated 3-Way Switch, Residential Grade, Grounding, Clear
reviews.text: Someone took an over exposed picture of this product because these things are extremely dim! You can hardly see them. I was expecting a pretty nice light to be emitted from it, with how cheap and bright LEDs are getting these days but Leviton is still stuck in the past century and only wants to rip people off. This is no brighter than the incandescent bulbs they had in some switches decades ago. I bet the bean counters at Leviton figured they'll save 2-3 cents per switch by going with the most underpowered LED they can, when sending specs to China for manufacturing these. That's why I try to avoid this company. Thanks Leviton, for letting me down once again!

reviews.text: I have been looking for this nearly 6 months. Leviton and other 3-way illuminated switches always flickered. These do have minimal flicker but not noticeable and compared the competition, they are rock solid. I did take off a star because it could be brighter but for the price, it's plenty good. There is another more expensive one that Leviton sells that is brighter but flickers. Oh well, it's not a perfect world. BTW, it's a very white light and most LED illuminated switches are yellow or orange or even red. White is a bit strange but it's fine.
